        0
      
    
    {\displaystyle f_{1}-f_{2}-f_{3}=0}
  . Moving 
  
    
      
        
          f
          
            3
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle f_{3}}
   to the other side of the equation gives the partial fraction decomposition 
  
    
      
        A
        =
        1
        ,
        B
        =
        −
        1
      
    
    {\displaystyle A=1,B=-1}
  .If 
  
    
      
        n
        =
        m
      
    
    {\displaystyle n=m}
   and 
  
    
      
        
          α
          
            i
          
        
        =
        
          α
          
            j
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \alpha _{i}=\alpha _{j}}
   for any 
  
    
      
        i
        ≠
        j
      
    
    {\displaystyle i\neq j}
  , then the alternant determinant is zero (as a row is repeated).If 
  
    
      
        n
        =
        m
      
    
    {\displaystyle n=m}
   and the functions 
  
    
      
        
          f
          
            j
          
        
        (
        x
